          <p><strong>Pronouns:</strong> They/Them</p>
          <p><strong>Symbol:</strong> Crescent moon with star inside</p>
          <p><strong>Colors:</strong> Midnight Blue &amp; Dream-Mist Gray</p>
          <p><strong>Animal:</strong> Luna Moth</p>
          <p><strong>Plant:</strong> Nightshade Blossom</p>
          <p><strong>Personality:</strong> Somnorys speaks in whispers and visions, weaving stories in the darkness behind closed eyes. Neither cruel nor kind, they simply reveal what already exists within, whether beautiful or terrifying.</p>
          <p><strong>Parents:</strong> <a href="#Mythora" class="relation-link">Mythora</a> and <a href="#Silvaris" class="relation-link">Silvaris</a></p>
          <p><strong>Spouse:</strong> <a href="#Rithmosa" class="relation-link">Rithmosa</a></p>
          <p><strong>Siblings:</strong> <a href="#Nythalos" class="relation-link">Nythalos</a></p>
          <p><strong>Children:</strong> <a href="#Animira" class="relation-link">Animira</a></p>
        </div>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <div id="Triumvira" class="card-triumvira">
          <img src="triumvira.png" alt="Triumvira Symbol">
          <h3>The Triumvira</h3>
          <p><strong>Domain:</strong> Fate, Destiny &amp; Life's Thread</p>
          <p><strong>Pronouns:</strong> They/Them (collective)</p>
          <p><strong>Symbol:</strong> Three interwoven threads</p>
          <p><strong>Aspects:</strong> Nascentia (Beginning), Tessa (Measure), Finalia (End)</p>
          <p><strong>Colors:</strong> Dawn Pink, Midday Gold &amp; Dusk Indigo</p>
          <p><strong>Animal:</strong> Raven</p>
          <p><strong>Plant:</strong> Flax</p>
          <p><strong>Personality:</strong> These three sisters move as one consciousness in three bodies, each complementing the others' work. They neither hurry nor delay, for all things unfold exactly as the pattern requires.</p>
          <p><strong>Origin:</strong> Born when Chronis' essence fragmented into three specialized forms</p>
          <p><strong>Parent:</strong> <a href="#Chronis" class="relation-link">Chronis</a></p>
          <p><strong>Spouse:</strong> None</p>
          <p><strong>Siblings:</strong> <a href="#Soltheron" class="relation-link">Soltheron</a>, <a href="#Lunthera" class="relation-link">Lunthera</a>, <a href="#Veydris" class="relation-link">Veydris</a>, and <a href="#Gemantra" class="relation-link">Gemantra</a></p>
          <p><strong>Children:</strong> None</p>
        </div>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <div id="Vinoryx" class="card-vinoryx">
          <img src="vinoryx.png" alt="Vinoryx Symbol">
          <h3>Vinoryx</h3>
          <p><strong>Domain:</strong> Wine, Intoxication &amp; Liberation</p>
          <p><strong>Pronouns:</strong> He/They</p>
          <p><strong>Symbol:</strong> Twisted grapevine with goblet</p>
          <p><strong>Colors:</strong> Wine Purple &amp; Ecstasy Gold</p>
          <p><strong>Animal:</strong> Leopard</p>
          <p><strong>Plant:</strong> Grapevine</p>
          <p><strong>Personality:</strong> Vinoryx dances on the edge of reason, their revelry both dangerous and divine. He liberates minds from constraints, bringing either blessed release or terrible madness—sometimes both at once.</p>
          <p><strong>Parents:</strong> <a href="#Corvanyx" class="relation-link">Corvanyx</a> and <a href="#Erythros" class="relation-link">Erythros</a></p>
          <p><strong>Spouse:</strong> None</p>
          <p><strong>Siblings:</strong> <a href="#Vovaris" class="relation-link"> Vovaris</a> and <a href="#Vindictrix" class="relation-link">Vindictrix</a></p>
          <p><strong>Children:</strong> None</p>
        </div>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <div id="Vovaris" class="card-vovaris">
          <img src="vovaris.png" alt="Vovaris Symbol">
          <h3>Vovaris</h3>
          <p><strong>Domain:</strong> Oaths, Promises &amp; Binding Words</p>
          <p><strong>Pronouns:</strong> He/Him</p>
          <p><strong>Symbol:</strong> Clasped hands bound by golden thread</p>
          <p><strong>Colors:</strong> Contract Parchment &amp; Binding Gold</p>
          <p><strong>Animal:</strong> Spider</p>
          <p><strong>Plant:</strong> Bindweed</p>
          <p><strong>Personality:</strong> Vovaris stands immovable where words hold power. Neither words nor weaseling can undo what has been sworn in his presence, and he watches all contracts with impartial, unwavering eyes.</p>
          <p><strong>Parents:</strong> <a href="#Erythros" class="relation-link">Erythros</a> and <a href="#Corvanyx" class="relation-link">Corvanyx</a></p>
          <p><strong>Spouse:</strong> None</p>
          <p><strong>Siblings:</strong> <a href="#Vinoryx" class="relation-link"> Vinoryx</a> and <a href="#Vindictrix" class="relation-link">Vindictrix</a></p>
          <p><strong>Children:</strong> None</p>
        </div>
